
[1]ferment

   FER'MENT, n. [L. fermentum, from fervo, to boil. See Fervent.]

   1. A gentle boiling; or the internal motion of the constituent parts of
   a fluid.

   [In this sense it is rarely used. See Fermentation.]

   2. Intestine motion; heat; tumult; agitation; as, to put the passions
   in a ferment; the state of people are in a ferment.

   Subdue and cool the ferment of desire.

   3. That which causes fermentation, as yeast, barm, or fermenting beer.
